OL,3,C'Much to do' on prison drug problems
OL,5,FInspection teams from Criminal Justice
OL,6,FInspection Northern Ireland (CJI), His
OL,7,FMajesty's Inspectorate of Prisons in
OL,8,FEngland and Wales (HMI Prisons), the
OL,9,FRegulation and Quality Improvement
OL,10,FAuthority (RQIA) and the Education and
OL,11,FTraining Inspectorate (ETI) undertook
OL,12,Fthe IRPs in October and November 2023.
OL,13,FThey examined progress against 12
OL,14,Fareas of concern identified during the
OL,15,F2022 unannounced inspection of
OL,16,FMaghaberry and 14 of the
OL,17,Frecommendations in the 2021 inspection
OL,18,Freport on Magilligan.JJacqui Durkin,
OL,19,Fchief inspector of criminal justice in
OL,20,FNorthern Ireland and Charlie Taylor,
OL,21,Fchief inspector of prisons in England
OL,22,Fand Wales, said overall they judged
OL,23,FMaghaberry to have made "reasonably
OL,24,Fgood progress".JThey expressed
OL,25,Fdisappointment that more progress has
OL,26,Fnot been made at Magilligan.JThe
